snippet: The launching by South Korea comes after Pyongyang conducted a series of its own missile tests, raising tensions on the Korean Peninsula.
abstract: South Korea conducts its own missile test amid rising military threats from North Korea, successfully launching newly developed ballistic missile capable of striking most of the North.
lead_paragraph: The launching by South Korea comes after Pyongyang conducted a series of its own missile tests, raising tensions on the Korean Peninsula.

headline.main: South Korea Tests Missile Able to Strike Most of North
